#import "../template.typ": *

= 1.13
Interpret the following in physical meaning for heat conduction.

(a) $u(0,t) = 0$

(b) $dvp(u(0,t),x) = 0$

(c) $dvp(u(0,t),x) - h u(0, t) = 0, dvp(u(L,t),x) + h u(L, t) = 0$
#solution[
(a) Temperature at $x=0$ always $0$.

(b) No heat flux at $x=0$, isolated.

(c) Heat flux on both boundaries, proportional to the difference in temperature between the medium and the surroundings.
]
